---
id: org.dxos.plugin.deck
name: DeckPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

The Deck plugin is the core layout engine for DXOS Composer. It manages the multi-plank workspace
("deck"), the sidebar, the complementary sidebar, dialogs, popovers, and toast notifications.
It owns the persisted and ephemeral layout state, handles URL routing, and implements every
`LayoutOperation` that changes what is visible on screen.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |

## Types

There is a single deck mode: presentation is derived from plank count and breakpoint rather than
stored. On desktop a singleton `active` renders `fullbleed`, exactly two planks render `tiling`
(flush proportional split), and three or more render `sliding`; below the `md` breakpoint the deck
is always `sliding` with full-viewport-width scroll-snapped planks. Fullscreen is a transient
overlay (`EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen`), not a mode.

```mdl
type DeckPresentation
  literals: fullbleed | tiling | sliding
```

```mdl
type PartAdjustment
  literals: close | companion | fullscreen | increment-start | increment-end
```

```mdl
type DeckState
  fields:
    active: string[]              # item IDs of the deck's planks; presentation derives from length + breakpoint
    inactive: string[]            # item IDs that have been closed; persisted for reopening
    plankSizing: Record<string, number>   # persisted plank widths in rem, keyed by item ID (sliding presentation only)
    tilingSizing?: number[]       # relative widths of tiled planks keyed by position (tiling split ratio); absent/empty means equal
    companionOpen: boolean        # whether the companion pane is visible
    companionFrameSizing: Record<string, number>  # companion frame widths in rem
    # NOTE: the selected companion variant and per-orientation split size live in react-ui-attention
    # view state (global, localStorage), not on DeckState — see util/companion-view-state.ts.
```

```mdl
type StoredDeckState
  desc: Persisted plugin state stored in KVS/localStorage.
  fields:
    sidebarState: closed | collapsed | expanded
    complementarySidebarState: closed | collapsed | expanded
    complementarySidebarPanel?: string
    activeDeck: string
    previousDeck: string
    decks: Record<string, DeckState>
```

```mdl
type EphemeralDeckState
  desc: Transient plugin state that is NOT persisted across sessions.
  fields:
    fullscreen?: string           # item ID of the plank currently displayed fullscreen (headless); never in the URL
    dialogOpen: boolean
    dialogType?: default | alert
    dialogBlockAlign?: start | center | end
    dialogContent?: { component: string; props?: any }
    popoverOpen: boolean
    popoverSide?: top | right | bottom | left
    popoverKind?: base | card
    popoverTitle?: string
    popoverContentRef?: string
    popoverContent?: { component: string } | { subject: any }
    toasts: Toast[]
    currentUndoId?: string
    scrollIntoView?: string
```

```mdl
type DeckSettings
  fields:
    showHints?: boolean           # show keyboard shortcut hints in the UI
    enableNativeRedirect?: boolean  # redirect supported URLs to the native desktop app
```

## Components

```mdl
component Matrix
  desc: |
    The primary workspace canvas. Renders `active` planks through a single Mosaic.Stack pipeline,
    styled by the presentation derived from plank count and breakpoint: fullbleed for one plank;
    tiling for exactly two (flush proportional split, hairline divider matching the solo companion
    splitter, draggable ratio); sliding for three or more (resizable, horizontally scrollable, a
    fixed inter-plank gap and edge shadow so planks read as stacked). Below the `md` breakpoint the
    deck is always sliding with full-viewport-width, non-resizable, scroll-snapped planks. In the
    sliding presentation planks pin to the viewport edges as slivers when scrolled past, and fold
    to a labeled vertical spine below the fold threshold; clicking a spine scrolls the plank back
    into view. Fullscreen is a transient overlay that replaces the whole stack with one plank,
    headless. Manages plank-resize handles and the companion pane alongside the attended plank.
  props:
    state: StoredDeckState        # persisted layout state atom
    ephemeral: EphemeralDeckState # transient state atom
  state:
    presentation: DeckPresentation   # derived from active.length + breakpoint, not stored
  actions:
    openPlank(id: string)
    closePlank(id: string)
    adjustPlank(id: string, type: PartAdjustment)
    resizePlank(id: string, size: number)
  layout: |
    ┌────────────┬────────────┬────────────┐
    │  sidebar   │  plank A   │  plank B   │
    │            │            │            │
    │            │  [content] │  [content] │
    │            │            │            │
    │            ├────────────┤            │
    │            │ companion  │            │
    └────────────┴────────────┴────────────┘
```

```mdl
component DeckSettings
  desc: Settings panel rendered in the Composer settings surface.
  props:
    settings: DeckSettings
  actions:
    updateSetting(key: string, value: any)
```

## Operations

```mdl
op Open
  desc: |
    Opens one or more subjects (item IDs or navigation paths) in the deck.
    `disposition` places them (see F-7): 'solo' — the default — navigates, so the deck becomes just
    the opened subjects, unless they are all already open (the existing plank scrolls into view);
    'add' inserts them as new planks, immediately after `pivotId` when provided (in-plank navigation
    anchors at its origin), else at the end of the deck; 'auto' follows the deck — it adds beside the
    origin (`pivotId`, falling back to the attended plank) when already sliding, and navigates solo
    otherwise, so in-plank/card navigation grows a sliding deck but replaces a solo one. Holding
    shift (forwarded as `modifiers.shift`) forces any disposition into an add — callers pass the raw
    modifier rather than encoding the policy, so the shift-forces-add rule lives only here. `key`
    replaces an existing plank sharing the key prefix in place. Validates each target against the app
    graph and redirects to a 404 node if not found. Fires ScrollIntoView, Expose, and an
    observability event for each newly opened item.
  input:
    subject: string[]             # item IDs or navigation paths to open
    disposition?: solo | add | auto  # solo (default) navigates; add inserts new planks; auto follows the deck
    modifiers?: { shift?: boolean }  # gesture modifiers; shift forces any disposition into an add
    pivotId?: string              # insert opened items immediately after this plank (add/auto)
    key?: string                  # replace an existing plank whose ID shares this key prefix
    workspace?: string            # switch to this workspace before opening
    navigation?: immediate        # skip validation; expand path only
    scrollIntoView?: boolean      # default true; set false to suppress auto-scroll
    state?: any
    variant?: string
  output: string[]
  effects: [echo:read, layout:state]
  requires: [AppGraph, AttentionCapabilities, ClientCapabilities, DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op Close
  desc: |
    Removes one or more subjects from the active deck.
    Computes which plank (if any) should receive attention after removal and
    schedules ScrollIntoView for it.
  input:
    subject: string[]
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities, AttentionCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdateSidebar
  desc: Update the sidebar visibility state (closed / collapsed / expanded).
  input:
    state?: closed | collapsed | expanded
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdateComplementary
  desc: Update the complementary-sidebar visibility state and optional panel selection.
  input:
    state?: closed | collapsed | expanded
    panel?: string
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdateDialog
  desc: |
    Show or hide the global dialog overlay. Accepts a surface component identifier
    or a boolean state flag. Propagates to EphemeralDeckState.
  input:
    subject?: string              # surface component identifier to display
    props?: any                   # props forwarded to the dialog surface
    state?: boolean               # false to close the dialog
    type?: default | alert
    blockAlign?: start | center | end
    overlayClasses?: string
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdatePopover
  desc: |
    Show or hide the global popover. Accepts anchor, content reference, or
    an explicit subject reference.
  input:
    subject?: any                 # subject reference to pass to the popover surface
    contentRef?: string           # surface component identifier for popover content
    anchorId?: string             # DOM element ID for positioning the popover anchor
    side?: top | right | bottom | left
    kind?: base | card
    title?: string
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdateCompanion
  desc: Update the companion-pane open state and active variant.
  input:
    open?: boolean
    variant?: string
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op AdjustPlank
  desc: |
    Apply a PartAdjustment to a specific plank (close, fullscreen, move, companion). 'fullscreen'
    toggles EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen for the given plank rather than mutating active.
  input:
    id: string
    type: PartAdjustment
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
  note: increment-start/increment-end remain implemented but their plank controls are hidden pending a reordering UX revisit.
```

```mdl
op UpdatePlankSize
  desc: Persist the width of a plank in rem.
  input:
    id: string
    size: number
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op UpdateTilingSize
  desc: |
    Persist the tiling split ratio as relative plank widths keyed by position (not plank ID), so
    swapping which plank occupies a slot keeps the layout.
  input:
    weights: number[]
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op AddToast
  desc: Push a toast notification into the ephemeral queue.
  input:
    title?: string
    body?: string
    duration?: number
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op ScrollIntoView
  desc: Schedule a subject to be scrolled into view when its plank mounts.
  input:
    subject: string
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op SwitchWorkspace
  desc: Switch the active workspace deck, persisting the previous workspace ID.
  input:
    subject: string               # workspace ID to switch to
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

```mdl
op RevertWorkspace
  desc: Revert to the previously active workspace.
  input: void
  output: void
  effects: [layout:state]
  requires: [DeckCapabilities]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Deck Presentations

  req F-1.1:
    when: the active deck changes length or the breakpoint changes
    then: presentation is derived, never stored — desktop renders fullbleed (1 plank), tiling (2),
          or sliding (3+); below the `md` breakpoint the deck is always sliding

  req F-1.2:
    when: presentation is sliding on desktop
    then: planks render side by side in a horizontally scrollable row, separated by a fixed
          inter-plank gap (a code constant, not a setting) with an edge shadow so planks read as
          stacked; each plank is user-resizable and its width is persisted in plankSizing

  req F-1.3:
    when: a sliding plank's width would exceed the viewport minus the space reserved for the other
          planks' spines
    then: its width is capped so its controls are never hidden behind pinned spines

  req F-1.4:
    when: a sliding plank is scrolled past a viewport edge
    then: it pins there as a sliver; once the visible sliver narrows below the fold threshold (one
          spine width plus the inter-plank gap) it folds to a vertical spine showing the plank's
          sigil and localized node label, animating in the plank's own travel direction

  req F-1.5:
    when: a folded spine is clicked
    then: the plank scrolls smoothly back into view and unfolds

  req F-1.6:
    when: presentation is tiling
    then: planks split the viewport width proportionally with no horizontal overflow or inter-plank
          gap, separated by a hairline divider matching the solo companion splitter; the ratio is
          draggable and persisted by position via UpdateTilingSize

  req F-1.7:
    when: the breakpoint is below `md` (mobile)
    then: planks are fixed full-viewport-width scroll-snap points, not user-resizable; the deck
          snaps one-to-next

  req F-1.8:
    when: subject is already present in the active deck
    then: deck is unchanged and the existing plank scrolls into view

  req F-1.9:
    when: viewing plank controls
    then: the reordering controls (increment-start / increment-end) are hidden pending a
          reordering UX revisit
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Fullscreen

  req F-2.1:
    when: user triggers AdjustPlank with type=fullscreen for a plank
    then: EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen is set to that plank's id; it fills the viewport headless
          (sidebar and heading chrome hidden), independent of how many planks are active

  req F-2.2:
    when: user triggers AdjustPlank with type=fullscreen for the currently-fullscreen plank
    then: EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen is cleared and the deck returns to its normal presentation

  req F-2.3:
    when: the app reloads
    then: fullscreen is not restored — it is transient and never persisted or reflected in the URL
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Sidebar & Complementary Sidebar

  req F-3.1:
    when: UpdateSidebar is dispatched with a new state
    then: sidebar transitions between closed / collapsed / expanded and state is persisted

  req F-3.2:
    when: UpdateComplementary is dispatched with a panel
    then: complementary sidebar opens to the specified panel
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Dialog & Popover Overlay

  req F-4.1:
    when: UpdateDialog is dispatched with a subject component
    then: the matching surface is rendered inside the global dialog overlay

  req F-4.2:
    when: UpdatePopover is dispatched with an anchorId
    then: popover is positioned relative to that DOM element

  req F-4.3:
    when: dialog or popover state is set to false
    then: overlay is closed and content is unmounted
```

```mdl
feat F-5: URL Navigation & Deep Linking

  desc: |
    The URL is a pair chain (`/w/<workspace>/<key>/<id>/…`) with one pair per plank path segment;
    id-less keys (singletons like `settings`, `members`) consume no id segment. Mapping is fully
    explicit: a graph node is URL-addressable only if its builder extension declares a `urlKey`
    plus either a static `urlPath` template (fixed-depth dynamic segments are `+`-encoded into the
    id) or a `resolve` effect for variable-depth subtrees (collections, native filesystem). There
    is no search fallback.

  req F-5.1:
    when: app loads with a URL referencing items
    then: DeckPlugin resolves each pair against the declared url mappings and opens the items in
          the deck

  req F-5.2:
    when: the active deck, attention, or companion selection changes
    then: browser URL is re-serialized from deck.active, appending the attended plank's open
          companion as `companion/<variant>`; attention itself is never serialized — on load it
          defaults to the last plank in the chain

  req F-5.3:
    when: an active plank's node declares no url mapping
    then: it is omitted from the URL and a warning is logged; no fallback representation is
          attempted

  req F-5.4:
    when: a navigation target cannot be resolved (unknown key, failed resolver, or missing node)
    then: Open operation redirects to a 404 node
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Toast Notifications

  req F-6.1:
    when: AddToast is dispatched
    then: a toast is appended to the queue and displayed for its configured duration

  req F-6.2:
    when: ShowUndo is dispatched
    then: a toast with an undo action is shown; invoking it executes the linked undo operation
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Navigation Model

  desc: |
    Interaction model replacing the former `navigationDefault` setting and replace-the-attended-plank
    behavior. Principle: stack semantics require a spatial anchor. On mobile the anchor is always
    the single visible plank, so all navigation is a journey stack. On desktop a nav-tree click has
    no anchor, so it gets browser semantics (plain click = navigate solo); stack semantics apply
    only where the origin is self-evident (links followed inside a plank). None of this is a
    user-facing mode: every rule keys off the gesture and the breakpoint, never off accumulated
    deck state, so behavior is identical whether one plank or many are open.
    STATUS: the desktop rules (F-7.1–F-7.4, F-7.7) are implemented; the mobile journey-stack rules
    (F-7.5, F-7.6) are a proposed design that remains unimplemented until the deck is fully mobile
    compliant — mobile currently shares the desktop behavior.

  req F-7.1:
    when: desktop — user plain-clicks an item in the nav tree
    then: the deck becomes just that plank (fullbleed), unless the item is already open — then the
          deck is unchanged and the existing plank scrolls into view; the previous arrangement is
          recoverable via browser history (deck state is pushed per change)

  req F-7.2:
    when: desktop — user modifier-clicks (or drags) an item from the nav tree
    then: the item is appended to the deck (or inserted at the drop position), scrolled into view,
          and attended; plain click retains its navigate-solo meaning regardless of deck size

  req F-7.3:
    when: desktop — user navigates to an object from inside a plank (an inline reference, its hover
          card, or a card's Open menu action / title)
    then: navigation follows the deck (Open with disposition 'auto', origin as pivotId or the
          attended plank) — when the deck is already sliding the target opens beside the originating
          plank; when the deck is solo it replaces the current plank; holding shift (where a
          modifier is available, e.g. the inline reference and hover card) always adds a new plank

  req F-7.4:
    when: desktop — user closes a plank
    then: only that plank closes (no cascade); closing the last plank shows the empty state

  req F-7.5:
    when: mobile (PROPOSED, unimplemented) — user navigates from any plank (nav drawer or in-plank link)
    then: the target is pushed after the current plank and slid into view; navigating from
          mid-stack first pops every plank after the current one

  req F-7.6:
    when: mobile (PROPOSED, unimplemented) — user closes a plank
    then: the plank and every plank after it are popped (the journey stack unwinds)

  req F-7.7:
    when: the attended plank folds to a spine (or leaves the viewport entirely, in the mobile snap
          presentation where planks are not pinned)
    then: attention moves to the unfolded plank nearest the viewport center; while the attended
          plank remains visibly usable, attention never changes on scroll (hysteresis — attention
          always points at something the user can see)
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Open subject beside an active plank
  given: deck has planks A and B active (tiling presentation, desktop)
  when: Open({ subject: ['C'], disposition: 'add' }) is dispatched
  then:
    - plank C is appended to the right of plank B
    - presentation becomes sliding (three planks)
    - browser URL reflects the new deck state
    - plank C is scrolled into view
```

```mdl
test T-2: Open with pivot insertion
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active
  when: Open({ subject: ['D'], disposition: 'add', pivotId: 'A' }) is dispatched
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, D, B, C]
    - no planks are closed
```

```mdl
test T-3: Open already-visible subject
  given: deck has plank A active
  when: Open({ subject: ['A'] }) is dispatched
  then:
    - active deck is unchanged
    - plank A scrolls into view
```

```mdl
test T-4: Enter fullscreen
  given: deck has planks [A, B] active
  when: AdjustPlank({ id: 'A', type: 'fullscreen' }) is dispatched
  then:
    - EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen is 'A'
    - only plank A is rendered, headless (sidebar and heading chrome hidden)
    - active is unchanged ([A, B])
```

```mdl
test T-5: Exit fullscreen
  given: EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen is 'A'
  when: AdjustPlank({ id: 'A', type: 'fullscreen' }) is dispatched
  then:
    - EphemeralDeckState.fullscreen is cleared
    - the deck returns to its normal presentation for the unchanged active list
```

```mdl
test T-6: Close plank
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active; B has attention
  when: Close({ subject: ['B'] }) is dispatched
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, C]
    - attention moves to an adjacent plank
    - ScrollIntoView is scheduled for the newly attended plank
```

```mdl
test T-7: Toast is shown and dismissed
  given: no toasts are in the queue
  when: AddToast({ title: 'Saved', duration: 3000 }) is dispatched
  then:
    - toast appears in the UI
    - toast is removed after 3 seconds
```

```mdl
test T-8: Two planks render tiling with a persisted split ratio
  given: deck has plank A active (fullbleed presentation, desktop)
  when: Open({ subject: ['B'], disposition: 'new-plank' }) is dispatched and the user drags the divider
  then:
    - presentation becomes tiling — A and B split the viewport with a hairline divider and no
      horizontal overflow
    - the new ratio is persisted in tilingSizing keyed by position via UpdateTilingSize
```

```mdl
test T-9: Sliding plank folds to a spine
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active (sliding presentation, desktop)
  when: user scrolls until plank A's visible sliver is narrower than the fold threshold
  then:
    - plank A folds to a vertical spine showing its sigil and localized node label
    - clicking the spine scrolls plank A back into view and unfolds it
```

```mdl
test T-10: Desktop nav-tree click navigates solo
  tags: [F-7]
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active (desktop)
  when: user plain-clicks item D in the nav tree
  then:
    - active deck becomes [D] (fullbleed presentation)
    - the previous arrangement [A, B, C] is restorable via browser back
```

```mdl
test T-11: Desktop modifier-click appends
  tags: [F-7]
  given: deck has planks [A, B] active (desktop)
  when: user modifier-clicks item C in the nav tree
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, B, C]
    - plank C is scrolled into view and attended

test T-11a: In-plank card navigation follows the deck (auto)
  tags: [F-7]
  given: a card navigation dispatches Open({ subject: ['C'], disposition: 'auto', pivotId: 'A' })
  when: the deck is solo [A]
  then:
    - active deck becomes [C] (replace — solo navigation)
  when: the deck is sliding [A, B]
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, C, B] (added beside the origin A)
  when: shift is held (disposition 'add') from solo [A]
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, C] (a new plank, never replacing)
```

```mdl
test T-12: Mobile branch from mid-stack pops forward
  tags: [F-7, proposed]
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active (mobile), B is the current plank
  when: user navigates to D from B
  then:
    - active deck becomes [A, B, D]
    - plank D slides into view
```

```mdl
test T-13: Attention follows scroll with hysteresis
  tags: [F-7]
  given: deck has planks [A, B, C] active (sliding presentation, desktop), A is attended
  when: user scrolls until plank A folds to a spine
  then:
    - attention moves to the unfolded plank nearest the viewport center
    - scrolling back so plank A unfolds does not move attention again
```

